It’s hardly news that football and fashion are intrinsically linked . There’s a long history of footballers taking their off-duty wardrobes just as seriously as their on-pitch performance, but the players of the 2026 World Cup are taking things to new heights. Team Spain? Head-to-toe Loewe. Team France? Arriving at the airport with Hermès bags in tow. Cristiano Ronaldo? Travelling with Gucci luggage, naturally.
Who would have thought we’d be saying this about the players rather than the WAGs, but here we are – frankly, we’re jealous of their handbag collections. It’s a go for the most fashionable World Cup yet.
