@rolex has opened its highest boutique in the world, perched more than 3,000 meters above sea level on Mount Titlis in the Swiss Alps. Getting there means taking a cable car up to the newly redeveloped Titlis Tower, a striking Herzog & de Meuron-designed structure with sweeping views of the glacier-covered summit and the Bernese Alps.⁠
⁠
Operated by Bucherer, the new space brings Rolex’s familiar retail codes into a pretty unbeatable alpine setting. The boutique sits alongside the Horizon Deck, Joseph’s Restaurant, and the Alpine Lounge, turning the mountaintop into a destination for travelers, watch lovers, and anyone who appreciates a very well-placed retail flex.⁠

@thenorthface has deflated its most famous creation, transforming the iconic Nuptse puffer into the Nuptse shirt. Stripping away the insulation but retaining much of the functionality, the summer-ready silhouette arrives in water-repellent recycled nylon with snap-button closures and the same short, wide fit that helped make the original a menswear favorite.⁠
⁠
The short-sleeve styles mirror the Nuptse’s signature two-tone color blocking, while a long-sleeve version reimagines the design in denim-look nylon. Essentially, it’s everything that makes the OG Nuptse great, just in shirt form. The catch? For now, it’s only available in Japan through Goldwin’s The North Face division.⁠

@lelabofragrances Santal 33 is already one of the most recognizable scents in modern fragrance, lingering everywhere from artisan coffee shops to Brooklyn sidewalks. More than a decade after becoming the brand’s breakout hit, the smoky, woody bestseller remains Le Labo’s top seller and continues to expand its reach.⁠
⁠
To mark its 20th anniversary, Le Labo is introducing a Santal 33 hand care kit, pairing a scented hand soap with a matching lotion infused with the fragrance’s signature cedarwood character. The launch joins an already growing Santal universe that includes shower gel, body bar, the original Santal 26 candle, and, most recently, Le Labo’s debut incense collection featuring handmade Kyoto-crafted sticks available in Santal 26, Encens 9, and Ambroxyde 17.⁠

